tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  85,2,"(And by the Promised Day) which is the Day of Judgement."
  85,4,"((Self-)destroyed were the owners of the ditch"
  85,7,"(And were themselves the witnesses) they used to testify that the believers were folk of error (of what they did to the believers) and it is said this means: they were present when they did this to the believers."
  85,9,"(Him unto Whom belongeth the Sovereignty) the stores (of the heavens) rain (and the earth) plants; (and Allah is of all things the Witness) He is the Witness over their works."
  85,12,"(Lo! the punishment of thy Lord) the seizure of your Lord of those who disbelieve in Him (is stern."
  85,17,"(Hath there come unto thee) O Muhammad-He asked His Prophet about this because He did not inform him about it before and then He did-(the story of the hosts"
  85,22,"(On a guarded tablet) He says: it is written on a tablet that is protected from the devils'."